      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be good. The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust and will soften during the day. The spring-like weather conditions from the late morning will give rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack in particular on steep sunny slopes below approximately 3000 m. <br/> The weather conditions fostered a stabilisation of the snow drift accumulations in particular on sunny slopes. <br/> In its middle, the snowpack is unfavourably layered. <br/> Adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind. There are large frames on the crest. <br/> Numerous medium-sized to large moist avalanches have been released in the last few days."
      },
